definitions.definition: A shieldmaiden and valkyrie in Germanic mythology , a main character in the Nibelungenlied , Völsunga saga , and some poems of the Poetic Edda .
A female given name from German .

subdefinitions.definition: Queen Brunhilda of Austrasia , wife of Sigebert I , who later ruled Austrasia and Burgundy as regent .

definitions.definition: 123 Brunhild , a main belt asteroid , named after the mythological figure.
